# AI Assistant Code Output Requirements

**Purpose**: Defines how the AI assistant should structure code changes and responses. Always applies when generating code.

## Code Generation Standards
- When implementing a feature: provide file list + exact code changes
- Ensure code compiles
- Avoid placeholder TODOs unless unavoidable; if used, explain them
- Never invent APIs. Use actual Apple frameworks. If unsure, propose a minimal approach
- Wrap debug print statements in `#if DEBUG` blocks for production builds

## Code Quality
- Prefer clarity over cleverness
- No metaprogramming or heavy generics unless necessary
- Do not introduce unnecessary frameworks or abstractions
- Prefer small, composable types
